						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in the temple of Satyamamba.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">9th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It refers to <hi rend="italic">daṇḍayara (daṇḍanāyaka)</hi> Mābale(ya) and to Taṁḍūru. Rest of the information is lost.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged fragment is in characters of about 9th century A.D. In its date portion only Āśhāḍamāsa, Sukla and Brihaspativāra (Thursday) can be read.</p>						

						</summary>
